==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Missionary
<hw>Mis"sion*ary</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Missionaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>missionnaire</ets>. See <er>Mission</er>, <pos>n</pos>.]</ety>
<def>One who is sent on a mission; especially, one sent to propagate
religion.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Missionary apostolic</b></col>, <cd>a Roman Catholic
missionary sent by commission from the pope.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Missionary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Missionary
<hw>Mis"sion*a*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to missions;
